text:
Hi  there, is it possible to use macros in dynamic templates that control the call of HubDB data as parameters? The following code does not work and renders the macro directly for the frontend. Is there any other way to achieve this?  Unfortunately, I cannot use modules because I can only include them but not edit them in the content editor.  All in all, I would like to avoid having to repeat the same code in my dynamic template, where only the query parameters change.
```{% macro image(parameter_1, parameter_2) %}
&lt;img src="{{parameter_1}}.{{parameter_2}}.url" alt="{{parameter_1}}.{{parameter_2}}.altText" width="{{parameter_1}}.{{parameter_2}}.width" style="max-width:100%; height:auto;" loading="lazy"&gt;
{% endmacro %}

{{ dynamicContent.image(item,image)  }}```
